print('File Handling\n')
#open or create a fie on same directory and write into it
myfile = open('Abc.txt',mode='w')
myfile.write('Hello World')
#to read a file 
myfile = open('Abc.txt') # default mode = 'r'
print(myfile.read())
#To append a new line to a file
myfile = open('Abc.txt',mode='a')
myfile.write('\nHie')
#again read
print('\nAfter Adding new line\n')
myfile = open('Abc.txt') # default mode = 'r'
print(myfile.read())


OUTPUT::

C:\Users\Admin>cd Desktop\kev

C:\Users\Admin\Desktop\kev>python Exp10.py

File Handling

Hello World

After Adding new line

Hello World
Hie

C:\Users\Admin>cd Desktop\kev>
